							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/seanhewitt/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/sean-hewitt-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/sean-hewitt-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Seán Hewitt" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/seanhewitt/">Seán Hewitt</a></h6>
										Seán Hewitt was born in 1990. He is the author of <em>J. M. Synge: Nature, Politics, Modernism</em> and the poetry collection <em>Tongues of Fire</em>, which was awarded the Laurel Prize and was shortlisted for the <em>Sunday Times</em> Young Writer of the Year Award, the John Pollard Foundation International Poetry Prize and a Dalkey Literary Award. He is the recipient of a Northern Writers’ Award, the Resurgence Prize and an Eric Gregory Award. Hewitt is a book critic for the <em>Irish Times</em> and teaches modern British and Irish literature at Trinity College Dublin.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
